SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781918292
OL,3,COne dead and dozens seriously injured
OL,4,Cas two trains collide near Bedford
OL,6,FPassenger Pete Knapp described people
OL,7,F"crying, screaming" and said some
OL,8,Fseemed to have major injuries.
OL,10,FThe 40-year-old told the Press
OL,11,FAssociation: "There was a moment of
OL,12,Fbeing flung into the chair in front,
OL,13,Fand then I saw smoke. People were
OL,14,Fcrying, screaming, people were so
OL,15,Fscared and confused.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@SO]sD@NOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781918292
OL,3,COne dead and dozens seriously injured
OL,4,Cas two trains collide near Bedford
OL,6,F"I got up and I saw a lot of people
OL,7,Fwho were unable to speak, had broken
OL,8,Flegs, and then I managed to get out of
OL,9,Fthe train and because I'm quite thin I
OL,10,Fwas able to squeeze out through the
OL,11,Fgap in the doors."
OL,13,FDr Knapp said he saw people with "life-
OL,14,Fthreatening, major injuries, minor
OL,15,Finjuries" as well as "people with
OL,16,Fbandages, people who couldn't see
OL,17,Fstraight", while others like him were
OL,18,Fstill able to walk.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@RO]uD@bOUwD@IO]wD@VOUyD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781918292
OL,3,COne dead and dozens seriously injured
OL,4,Cas two trains collide near Bedford
OL,6,FHe said: "I've got blood all over my
OL,7,Ftrousers and my back hurts like hell
OL,8,Fbut I'm all right."
OL,10,FHe said he had not felt the train slow
OL,11,Fdown before the crash but other
OL,12,Fpassengers told him they had.
OL,14,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer
OL,15,Fdescribed the crash as "hugely
OL,16,Fconcerning" and said he is "grateful
OL,17,Fto the emergency services for their
OL,18,Fswift response to this tragic
OL,19,Fincident".
OL,26,@nD@JOUpD@SO]wD@XOUxD@KO]xD@\OU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
